HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 995
By Hicks G
A RESOLUTION to commend Tennessee credit unions for their
support of the Tennessee Financial Literacy
Commission.
WHEREAS, it is our privilege to recognize those institutions whose altruistic vision
guides them to support initiatives that greatly benefit the citizens of this State; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee credit unions have made a three-year financial commitment,
totaling $1.8 million, in support of the Tennessee Financial Literacy Commission (TNFLC),
which was created by the General Assembly in 2010; and
WHEREAS, over the last century, credit unions in Tennessee have built a legacy of
serving individuals and helping build Tennessee communities, assisting credit union members
with their needs, and guiding them through responsible stewardship of their money; and
WHEREAS, the TNFLC shares the same goals, and with this partnership with
Tennessee credit unions, the TNFLC will be able to provide additional teacher training and
certification, classroom materials, interactive curricula, and community scholarships, expanding
upon the success it has achieved to date, which includes programs such as Money Week; and
WHEREAS, the partnership between the TNFLC and Tennessee credit unions is one
that will bring increased awareness of the importance of personal finance to citizens throughout
the State, enabling them to make informed money decisions that will shore up their lives and
their futures; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we honor these devoted institutions for their good work
toward improving the well-being of Tennesseans through financial literacy; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we commend Tennessee credit unions for their support of the Tennessee
